metadata.name: Arbitrum One Bridge
metadata.description:
The Arbitrum Bridge is the native bridge of the Arbitrum rollup, which allows any ERC-20 asset to be bridged from Ethereum mainnet into Arbitrum One.
The bridge inherits the security of Ethereum, although the Arbitrum maintains upgrade keys which can change the bridge code.

metadata.name: Avalanche Bridge
metadata.description:
The Avalanche Bridge allows assets to be bridged from the Ethereum and Bitcoin blockchains to the Avalanche C-Chain.
The bridge is secured by an Intel SGX secure enclave, which validates the deposit/withdrawal events on the various chains.

metadata.name: Gnosis Chain Bridge
metadata.description:
The Gnosis Chain's native bridge bridges Dai from Ethereum into xDai, the native asset of Gnosis Chain. Additionally, the Gnosis Chain OmniBridge allows any ERC-20 asset to be bridged from Ethereum.
Bridge validators observe events on both chains and relay messages to the bridge contract. Bridge validators are selected by the 6 members of the Bridge Governance Board.

Multichain is a protocol for routing messages and assets across various blockchains using a network of distributed nodes.
metadata.securityModel: Multichain relies on a network of individual nodes (described as "MPC Network") to monitor network activity. These nodes aggregate signatures off-chain to generate the on-chain transactions needed to facilitate the bridge activity. The number of signers, their identities, as well as the signer selection process is unknown at this time.
